{
  "stem": "3212.1",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Because later on, when I met Germans, it was very hard for me to understand them.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It's a dialect.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "You know, farmers dialect, or Viennese.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But this was a little bit, even, different, because it's a dialect that, in little villages and Austrians that-- actually, when you write it, it's German.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But when you speak it, it's a little bit different.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I didn't speak Yiddish, no.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The only thing I knew is Viennese Austrian.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And we started, when I went once or twice in a week, when I went to the other village for religious lessons, we were starting to read the Bible in Hebrew.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But I could read it, but I didn't understand what I was reading.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I enjoyed learning Hebrew.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I enjoyed to learn about-- a little bit about history.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I enjoyed, at home, the religious holiday.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Especially when we went to the temple, to my grandma, to Luckenbach.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "When we were together with the whole family, and I get my noodle soup, and my special food.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "It was very-- a very happy time.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And all my childhood, in Schwarzenbach was a very healthy childhood.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "From school.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I had a lot of non-Jewish friends-- neighbors, and-- and from school, girls and boys.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And we had a good time, always.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "In winter or summer, we're-- we were going in the mountains, we were sliding down the snow hills.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And in summer, too, many times I went with my father, with the horses to bring fruit, or wood he need for the bakery.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Or he dealt with-- with the lumber, too.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So we had to go to other villages, like Luckenbach, Deutschkreutz, to different places.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "So he loaded the wagon with the-- with lumber very high.",
      "word_count": 11
    }
  ],
